UK rate rise needed before election - George . Governor of the Bank of England Eddie George said on Thursday he saw no need for a dramatic UK interest rate rise but expected to see a rate rise before the general election . " We don ' t see an urgent need for a dramatic step , " he toldthe House of Commons Treasury Select Committee . But when asked if did not foresee a rate rise before the general election he said , " I certainly wouldn ' t go that far " . A general election must be held by May 1997 . - - Rosemary Bennett + 44 171 542 7715 
